FBIS3-15997 "drsov048_f_94006" FBIS-SOV-94-048 Document Type:Daily Report 11 Mar 1994 National Affairs `Reforms for People' Bloc Established WS1003200394 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in Ukrainian 1900 GMT 10 Mar 94 WS1003200394 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network Language: Ukrainian Article Type:BFN [Text] A Reforms for People bloc was established in Ukraine. It comprises the [word indistinct] experts from various branches of industry, specialists, and workers from key regions of our state. The aim of the new bloc is to stabilize the economy by implementing real market reforms, to increase the incomes of the population at the expense of reforming the financial and money systems and cutting down the nonproduction expenditures of the budget, to combat crime and corruption, and to protect rights and (?honor) of individuals. The bloc is headed by well-known Ukrainian economist Volodymyr Lanovyy, president of the Center for Market Reforms.
